FBIS3-1381 "drafr059_e_94006" FBIS-AFR-94-059 Document Type:Daily Report 27 Mar 1994 WEST AFRICA Nigeria Abacha Leaves for Group of 15 Summit in India AB2703091594 Lagos Radio Nigeria Network in English 0600 GMT 27 Mar 94 AB2703091594 Lagos Radio Nigeria Network Language: English Article Type:BFN [Text] The head of state, General Sani Abacha, left Abuja this morning at the head of a Nigerian delegation to the summit of the Group of 15 which opens tomorrow in New Delhi, India. He is being accompanied by the ministers of external affairs, Alhaji Babagana Kingibe; works and housing, Alhaji Lateef Jakande; and that of finance, Dr. Kalu Idika Kalu, as well as other top government officials. A Radio Nigeria State House correspondent reports that the summit of the Group of 15, which is an economic community of developing nations, will end on Wednesday [30 March].
